    "notes": "Scottish English. Rhotic (unlike RP). Scottish Vowel Length Rule (SVLR): vowels long only before /r, v, ð, z/ and morpheme-final position. /x/ phonemic (loch [lɔx]). No TRAP-BATH split. FOOT-STRUT often merged. Scots (a related language) has additional distinct features. Source: Wells (1982) vol. 2.",
